Hi! First up, I’m using a throwaway because I find this issue quite embarrassing. Some info about me:
Female, 24, Australian, 165cm, 56kg.
On Brenda OCP and I have a Mirena IUD for treatment of endometriosis. 
On 20mg of roaccutane a day for severe acne.
On 100mg of Zoloft a day for depression and anxiety.

So, basically. I keep getting cysts under my armpit. One comes up, I go see a doctor, they give me antibiotics, it goes away, it comes back up (usually in a slightly different area of the armpit) a couple of weeks later. This cycle has been going on for approximately 6 months. 
I occasionally get smaller ones that go down without antibiotics under my other armpit. I’m done with it. 
They’re small, probably only 2cm in diameter, but they’re incredibly painful. 
I shave my armpits, and I’ve made sure to use a disposal razor and use a new one EACH TIME I shave so I’m not getting any germs from a dirty razor when I shave.  I’m a very clean gal, I shower everyday. 
I don’t know what’s causing it and what I can do. I have two at the moment, and they’re incredibly painful. What can I do? Why is this happening?
